I couldn’t even get into a University.

I was the epitome of a fixed mindset.
Until… I read Mindset by Carol Dweck.

It fundamentally changed me as a human.
It taught me that anyone can learn and grow.

But only if I was willing to put in the work.
Only if I was willing to apply themselves.

It also taught me that we are never stagnant.
We are never neutral.

We are either green and growing.
Or ripe and rotting.

What are you growing towards this week?

The past 2 weeks have been INSANE, but I am so grateful for it all. From closing on my first house in ATX with my brother, running the LA Marathon, & experiencing my 1st @hpltraining weekend. It has been crazy!!

A lot people have been asking me how I am able to do so much and keep my positive energy going. 

The short answer. 

I am fueled by GRATITUDE & PATIENCE. I have accomplished some awesome things, but I don’t allow those things to define me. There is always more work to be done and if you’re playing the “long game” you will realize time is in your favor. 

I’ve learned that life is a big game of PERSPECTIVE. 

Regardless of your circumstances, if you truly understood that most people in this world have it tougher than you. It would be much easier to keep a positive framework. We all have our shortcomings, but there are millions of people that don’t have access to clean drinking water. That’s where my mind goes if I’m not “feeling it” on a particular day. If you have access to even read this post… you are so much more fortunate that millions of people. 

It also helps when you change your environment and the people you listen to. @hpltraining is a great example of that, surround yourself with likeminded humans and watch what happens. If you don’t have the mindset yet, start to develop it on your own time!

My focus is on doing the things that FIRE my soul up. The things that seem like “work” to others, but it’s “play” for me. Thats how I keep a positive mindset. 

You are 100% responsible for your life and happiness. Take control of it. Don’t point the finger at anyone else, but yourself.

His attitude toward life, business, and family is infectious, and any creator or business owner looking to refocus on "building the foundation" will take a lot of value from this conversation.

By the time you finish listening to this conversation, we hope you ask yourself two questions: 1) when was the last time you turned a failure into a win and 2) do you know who you are? - if you don't have a good answer to either question it's okay! We challenge you to take a risk on something you feel you have been putting off or want to do.

3 Benefits of Sprinting for Marathon Runners🚀

1. Improved Running Economy: Sprinting helps enhance overall running economy, which refers to the efficiency of your running stride. By working on your sprinting abilities, you can develop better form, stride length, and power generation. 

2. Muscle Strength & Power: Sprinting engages fast twitch muscle fibers that may not be as heavily used during long distance running. Incorporating sprint workouts can help strengthen these fibers and increase muscle power. This added strength can be beneficial during the latter stages of a marathon when fatigue sets in. 

3. Enhanced Anaerobic Capacity: Sprinting is an anaerobic activity that primarily relies on stored energy sources rather than oxygen. While marathon running is predominantly aerobic, having a higher anaerobic capacity can help marathon runners during the occasional intense surge or incline in a race. It can also aid in having a “kick” to finish a race.

I also love how I get to see so many familiar faces at marathons. At times I see my running friends more than family or childhood friends. It’s such an amazing thing to have a shared interest with people that brings you all over the world. I always say this and it couldn’t be more true… “The running community is everywhere!”

• COMMUNITY
It’s the smallest things that make the most impact when you’re chasing after a big goal. The support from strangers, friends, & family play a major role to allow you to continue moving forward. This apple farmer graciously offered us some apples along our journey to Busan and it gave us a ton of energy. It was the highlight of my day, once he heard we were running to Busan his eyebrows raised. These small rural towns don’t get too many foreigners that visit, but this small interaction gave me a boost to continue my journey! You never know how one positive moment can change the trajectory of your story. 

• CONFIDENCE
How do you build mental toughness? This is something I always get asked and something I continue to ponder. It’s not just about running miles or lifting weights. It’s about being a man of your word. It’s like the old saying, “Your word is your bond.” When you say you’re going to do something, do it. The more proof you have that you actually will do what you say you’re going to do is how CONFIDENCE is developed. 

• POSITIVE SELF TALK 
It’s okay to have high expectations of yourself. No one should care more than you. How we speak to ourselves is truly the most important conversation. Not only in times of success, but also during times of failure. After facing fatigue and pain running up a mountain, I found the one thing that allowed me to continue moving forward was having a positive mantra. The inner conversation we have is one we have power to control.
